Ellie was found wandering the streets of Houston, searching for food and shelter from freezing temperatures. Her short 4-5 years of life have not been kind to her. Her beautiful wavy fur was covered in years of dirt. Her ears were infected and causing her discomfort. She had been ignored by those who saw her, and looked the other way. From here on, this gentle little girl will know what it feels like to be loved and enjoy her life as someone's furry family member. She's a perfect little package of sweetness, ready to share her love.
Ellie is a very calm, easy going girl. She does well on a leash and enjoys walks. She doesn't need a hustle and bustle lifestyle. She is content just chilling out with her family watching TV, taking car rides to get a cheeseburger, and getting lots of cuddles and belly rubs. During her photo session she did not care about playing with toys, she just wanted to be petted and loved on.
Ellie looks like she is a small flat coat retriever mix, she is now spayed, up to date on vaccinations and microchipped.
